main event: Two witnesses observed a single object in the sky, described as having 2 white lights and traveling at a high altitude in a north-south direction.
interesting points: The object was approximately 2/3 the diameter of the moon,It moved irregularly and was visible for about 2-3 minutes,The witnesses were unable to provide detailed information about the object due to its speed and altitude,The case has been classified as UNIDENTIFIED, The analysis suggested that the sighting was likely that of a meteor or falling satellite.
